{
  "texts": [
    "In this context, new nodes and classes are continuously integrated into the existing graph structure, resulting in a distribution shift compared to the original graph being condensed.",
    "To adapt the condensed graph to these dynamic distribution shifts and manage graph data over an extended period, OpenGC employs temporal data augmentation to simulate evolving graph patterns and create multiple structure-aware environments.",
    "Furthermore, it incorporates invariance learning regularization in GC to preserve the invariant patterns across different temporal environments in the condensed graph.",
    "By this means, OpenGC significantly enhances the adaptability of downstream GNNs by training them on the temporally generalized condensed graph, eliminating the need to laboriously design specific generalization modules for each GNN.",
    "C. Efficient Graph CondensationThe GC process requires significant computational resources."
  ]
}